## Current State

```
app/example/lib/src/
├── bootstrap/               # Module composition
├── di/                      # GetIt → Riverpod bridge (infra providers)
├── shared/
│   ├── constants/           # App-wide constants
│   └── theme/               # App theme tokens
├── features/
│   ├── authentication/      # Full auth domain + UI (currently monolithic)
│   │   ├── data/
│   │   │   ├── datasources/ # IAuthLocalDataSource, AuthLocalDataSource
│   │   │   ├── models/      # UserModel
│   │   │   └── repositories/ # AuthRepositoryImpl
│   │   ├── domain/
│   │   │   ├── entities/    # UserEntity
│   │   │   ├── failures/    # AuthFailure
│   │   │   ├── repositories/ # IAuthRepository ← only features/authentication uses this
│   │   │   ├── usecases/    # LoginUseCase, LogoutUseCase, GetCurrentUserUseCase
│   │   │   └── value_objects/ # Username, Password
│   │   ├── presentation/
│   │   │   ├── notifiers/   # LoginNotifier, HomeNotifier
│   │   │   ├── screens/     # LoginScreen, HomeScreen
│   │   │   ├── state/       # LoginState
│   │   │   └── widgets/     # CustomButton, CustomTextField, LoadingOverlay
│   │   └── di/              # auth_providers.dart
│   ├── network_demo/
│   └── settings/
└── router/                  # app_router.dart
```

**Problem:** `HomeNotifier` and `LoginNotifier` hold session state locally. Any other feature needing to know "is user logged in?" or inject a token must cross feature boundaries or duplicate logic.

